# markdownlint walks any glob it's given verbatim and doesn't read
# .gitignore. To avoid scanning vendored upstream READMEs and
# build outputs, the canonical invocation is:
#
#     markdownlint -c .markdownlint.json $(git ls-files '*.md')
#
# That way only TRACKED .md files get linted; vendored deps and
# build outputs are skipped because they're already gitignored.
# Working-tree scratchpads (TODO.md, FUTURE.md, etc., gitignored at
# root via *.md) ARE linted locally because they live in your tree;
# CI doesn't see them because CI runs against the index.
#
# This file stays as a fallback for tools that pass plain globs to
# markdownlint (e.g. editor integrations).

